    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Recursion Demonstration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    margin: 2em;\n    background: #f0f8ff;\n    color: #333;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    color: #005f99;\n  }\n  #output {\n    background: #e1ecf4;\n    border: 1px solid #a8c7e7;\n    padding: 1em;\n    margin-top: 1em;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    font-family: monospace;\n    max-height: 300px;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n  }\n  button {\n    background-color: #007acc;\n    border: none;\n    color: white;\n    padding: 0.6em 1.2em;\n    text-align: center;\n    text-decoration: none;\n    font-size: 1em;\n    border-radius: 0.3em;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    transition: background-color 0.3s;\n  }\n  button:hover {\n    background-color: #005f99;\n  }\n  label {\n    display: inline-block;\n    margin-right: 0.5em;\n  }\n  input[type=number] {\n    width: 4em;\n    font-size: 1em;\n    padding: 0.2em;\n    margin-right: 1em;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Recursion Demonstration: Factorial Function</h1>\n\n<p>\n  Recursion is a programming technique where a function calls itself to solve smaller instances of a problem until a base case is reached.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  In this example, we calculate the factorial of a number <em>n</em>, defined as:\n</p>\n\n<pre>\nfactorial(n) = n × factorial(n - 1) if n > 1\nfactorial(1) = 1  (base case)\n</pre>\n\n<label for=\"numberInput\">Enter a positive integer (1–15):</label>\n<input type=\"number\" id=\"numberInput\" min=\"1\" max=\"15\" value=\"5\" />\n<button id=\"runBtn\">Run Recursion</button>\n\n<div id=\"output\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-label=\"Recursion output log\"></div>\n\n<script>\n  const output = document.getElementById('output');\n\n  function factorial(n, depth = 0) {\n    // Indent to visualize recursive call depth\n    const indent = '  '.repeat(depth);\n    output.textContent += `${indent}factorial(${n}) called\\n`;\n    \n    if (n === 1) {\n      output.textContent += `${indent}Base case reached: factorial(1) = 1\\n`;\n      return 1;\n    } else {\n      const result = n * factorial(n - 1, depth + 1);\n      output.textContent += `${indent}Returning: ${n} * factorial(${n - 1}) = ${result}\\n`;\n      return result;\n    }\n  }\n\n  document.getElementById('runBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {\n    output.textContent = '';\n    const n = parseInt(document.getElementById('numberInput').value, 10);\n    if (isNaN(n) || n < 1 || n > 15) {\n      output.textContent = 'Please enter a positive integer between 1 and 15.';\n      return;\n    }\n    output.textContent += `Computing factorial of ${n} recursively...\\n\\n`;\n    const result = factorial(n);\n    output.textContent += `\\nFactorial(${n}) = ${result}`;\n  });\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
